MainClaim.text: The exclusive use of open, public data in risk-based border checks does not necessarily mitigate the ethical concerns related to risk-based checks on travelers.

Untitled 1.text: The use of OSINT in border checks can help to identify and assess security risks in a fairly traditional manner.

Untitled 2.text: OSINT can be used to differentiate the revelatory function as part of a risk classification of travelers.

Untitled 3.text: The use of OSINT in situational risk assessment does not preclude fundamental forms of ethical impact.

Untitled 4.text: The use of OSINT in risk profiling does not preclude fundamental forms of ethical impact.

Untitled 5.text: The ethical impact of OSINT practices in border checks depends on the situational details of the implementation.
